title: Valdez to return from Thailand Feb. 25 for SEAG tryout
text:
Valdez to return from Thailand Feb. 25 for SEAG tryout By Joey Villar (philstar.com)   4:29pm Alyssa Valdez 
MANILA, Philippines â€“ Not even distance could stop Alyssa Valdez from playing for flag and country. 
Valdez will fly to the country on February 25 to try out for a spot in the national team in Davao City and will return the next day to Thailand where she is currently playing for 3BB Nakornnont in the Thai League. 
"She will arrive very early on February 25 to try out in Davao and will fly back to Thailand on Feb. 26," said the Phl V-League's Ricky Palou after talkiing to the former Ateneo star and the face of Phl volleyball. 
It was a promise Valdez made to Larong Volleyball sa Pilipinas, Inc. acting president Peter Cayco before the former left the country last month. 
Valdez failed to make the first phase of the tryout conducted by coach Francis Vicente early this month at the Arellano U Gym in Pasay City because of her previous commitment to suit up with 3BB. 
There, Valdez made history by becoming the first Filipino to ever suit up as an import.   
Valdez is eyeing her second tour of duty with the national squad seeing action in the Southeast Asian Games in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia set August 19-31 after serving as the team captain and the Phl delegation's flag-bearer in the last SEAG in Singapore two years ago. 
She is expected to join some of the country's top players headed by Jaja Santiago, Jovelyn Gonzaga, Aby Marano and Rachel Ann Daquis among others.
